<p>These bindings come straight from <code>src/lib/keyboard-shortcuts.ts</code>. The page is rebuilt on every deploy, so it's always in sync with the app.</p>

<p>On macOS the modifiers show as <kbd>⌘</kbd> (Cmd), <kbd>⌃</kbd> (Ctrl), <kbd>⌥</kbd> (Option), <kbd>⇧</kbd> (Shift). On Linux / Windows the same actions use <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> / <kbd>Alt</kbd> / <kbd>Shift</kbd>.</p>

<div class="callout callout--tip">
  <div class="callout-title">Customize</div>
  <div class="callout-body">Open <strong>Settings → Shortcuts</strong> to rebind any editable action. Disabled bindings show <code>editable: false</code> in the source and are reserved for the number-row shortcuts.</div>
</div>

{%- for group in shortcuts %}
<h2 id="{{ group.key }}">{{ group.label }}</h2>
<table class="shortcut-table">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Action</th>
      <th>macOS</th>
      <th>Linux / Windows</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
{%- for a in group.actions %}
    <tr>
      <td>{{ a.label }}</td>
      <td><kbd>{{ a.mac }}</kbd></td>
      <td><kbd>{{ a.other }}</kbd></td>
    </tr>
{%- endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{%- endfor %}
